result.execSummary:
The defendant Cassandra L. Edge was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Cassandra L. Edge is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges. On one or more other charges, Cassandra L. Edge was found not guilty. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Cassandra L. Edge is presumed innocent of the not guilty charges.

  • Cassandra L. Edge was found guilty of Theft-Movable Property <=$2500 [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).
  • Cassandra L. Edge was found guilty of Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

State recommends 2 years probation for Ct 2 and 1 year probation for Ct 7 with the following conditions: to pay costs on Ct 7 and waive costs on Ct 2, to pay restitution in the amount of $192.96, to work full time, if on disability to work part time or seek work, provide DNA sample, to have no contact with M.E. and T. S. unless approved by DOC, and to submit to random UAs. Attorney Frank heard. Defendant heard. Court heard and orders 2 years probation for each count with the following conditions: for Ct 2 to pay restitution of $162.96- cash bond to be applied, court waives costs for Ct 2, court costs for Ct 7, not to have any contact with M.E. or T.S. unless expressly approved by DOC, not to posses or consume any alcohol, not to possess or consume any controlled substance unless prescribed and to be taken only as prescribed, to submit to random observed testing for controlled substances upon request of law enforcement, DOC, or designee, to provide a DNA sample, to complete mental health treatment consistent with recommendation of providers. Court does not object to transfer probation to IA or IL. If revoked, 2 days credit.
